name: Dan Rhatigan
# portrait: 
url: http://ultrasparky.org
bio: <p>Dan Rhatigan is a designer, teacher, and long-time blogger. Originally from New York City, he moved to the UK to study typeface design at the University of Reading. Despite his opinions about most British food, he now lives in London and works for Monotype Imaging as a senior type designer. He also lectures on typography and branding in the Netherlands and the UK, and publishes a zine called Pink Mince. You can look at some of his other work at <a href="http://ultrasparky.org">ultrasparky.org</a></p>
